Durban - Phoenix triple murder accused Colin Pillay appeared in the Verulam Magistrate's Court on Wednesday. Indictments were expected to be served but the matter was adjourned to next Wednesday. Pillay, 45, a former tow truck driver, faces charges of three counts of premeditated murder and one of robbery with aggravating circumstances. He is accused of killing Phoenix mother Jane Govindsamy, 45, an employee at a logistics company and her daughters Denisha, 22, and Rackelle, 16,  Grade 11 pupil at Rydal Park Secondary. Their bodies were found by their father Sagren Govindsamy at their home in Longcroft, Phoenix on September 21. Pillay was arrested the following morning at a bed and breakfast in Palmview. In a previous interview with POST Jane's sister Annie Ganasparsdh said all they wanted was justice. "We want a full sentence for this crime and we appeal to anyone with information which can assist with the investigation to come forward." Pillay has remained in police custody since his arrest. POST 